If you upgrade to the latest version of Streamlit you'll be able to pass a custom hash_func to hash your generator. See example below.
<denchmark-code>import types
import streamlit as st

@st.cache(hash_funcs={types.GeneratorType: id})
def x():
   return (a for a in range(10))

st.write(list(x()))
</denchmark-code>

See <denchmark-link:https://docs.streamlit.io/advanced_caching.html#the-hash-funcs-parameter>hash_funcs docs</denchmark-link>
